.TH "slim_write" 9 "slim_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
slim_write \- Write SLIMbus value element
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" slim_write
.BI "(struct slim_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "u32 addr "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ","
.BI "u8 *val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
client handle.
.IP "addr" 12
address in the value element to write.
.IP "count" 12
number of bytes to write. Maximum bytes allowed are 16.
.IP "val" 12
value to write to value element
.SH "RETURN"
-EINVAL for Invalid parameters, -ETIMEDOUT If transmission of
this message timed out (e.g. due to bus lines not being clocked
or driven by controller)
